## ⚠️ Vulnerabilities Summary

- Default Credentials (guest:guest)  
- BOPLA (Privilege escalation)  
- SSRF (Banner URL injection)  
- Sensitive Data Exposure (Internal APIs)  
- LFI (profile image parameter)  
- Weak Passwords (SSH brute force)  

---

## 🧠 Key Takeaways

- Always test for privilege escalation after login  
- SSRF can expose internal services  
- Internal APIs often leak sensitive data  
- LFI can lead to credential discovery  
- Weak passwords are still common  

---

## 🏁 Attack Chain Summary

```
Recon → Default Creds → BOPLA → SSRF → Internal API → Credential Leak → LFI → SSH → Flag
```

---

## 📌 Conclusion

This lab demonstrates a full attack chain combining multiple vulnerabilities to achieve system compromise. It highlights the importance of secure API design, input validation, and proper authentication controls.
